    "bio": "Herman Armstrong (@TheRevWrites) is an adaptive leadership coach specializing in cross-cultural communication and the Executive Director of a Christian nonprofit dedicated to racial reconciliation. He also leads the Kathairo Leadership Collective, where he equips leaders through adaptive coaching that fosters cultural clarity, effective communication, and organizational health. Currently pursuing a Doctor of Ministry in leadership, Herman also holds the Harvard Certificate in School Management and Leadership (CSML). He writes at Kathairo.com on the intersections of leadership, culture, and faith.",
    "presentationExperience": "I have served as a keynote speaker and facilitator for professional conferences, universities, and organizational development sessions, consistently focusing on the intersection of intercultural competence and relational leadership. My experience ranges from lecturing graduate students on the foundations of leadership to leading high-stakes professional development workshops for schools and nonprofits, where I help teams navigate internal conflict and cultural blind spots. By utilizing data-driven frameworks like the Intercultural Development Inventory (IDI), I provide audiences with a roadmap to move from transactional management to transformational, high-trust leadership.",
