    "sessionDescription": "This session explores how classroom practices and instructional language can unintentionally prioritize compliance and content delivery over meaningful student engagement. Grounded in current Student-Centered Learning (SCL) research, Dr. Ken Patterson will share practical, justice-centered strategies that help educators create equitable, inclusive, and relationship-driven learning environments for all students. Participants will examine how daily teacher decisions influence belonging, engagement, and achievement while leaving with immediately applicable practices that support authentic student learning and success across diverse educational settings.",
