    "name": "Dr. Pallavi Chhabra & Dr. Kacy Shahid",
    "role": "Postdoctoral Research Associate",
    "organization": "Washington University in St. Louis",
    "bio": "Dr. Pallavi Chhabra is a Postdoctoral Research Associate at Washington University in St. Louis. Her work focuses on bridging the gap between research and practice to inform the design and implementation of equitable learning opportunities and policies in various educational contexts. Dr. Kacy Shahid is a compassionate and motivational leader dedicated to fostering identity-affirming, inclusive environments.",
    "presentationExperience": "Chhabra, P., Alexandra, B., Wentworth, L., & Mercado-Garcia, (2025, July 23-25). The art of the bridge: Real-world brokering in action. [Panel session]. NNERPP Annual Forum, St. Louis, MO. \nChhabra, P. & Wilson, T. (2025, April). Mapping the Spatial Inequalities in Missouri’s School\nDiscipline Policies. [Paper presentation] Mapping Spaces, Embodying Territories Conference at Saint Louis University, St. Louis, MO \nPowers, M.K., Chhabra, P., Molloy, M.C., Medler, A.C. (2026, April 8-12). Where are the gaps? A Systematic literature review on strategies to address chronic absenteeism. [Accepted Roundtable presentation]. Annual meeting of American Educational Research Association, Los Angeles, CA.",
